channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "With partying, it's like there's not a lot of people like teaching how to sort of do that thing. So you just kind of either do it or you have a mentor. So what was that process like for you? I mean, I learned how to plan and put events together in the military. You know, those skills that came in handy and then stumbled upon the social circle blueprint and those types of things. I read through all that stuff. I had friends, actually, that were close friends of mine that had thrown really good events. Before I even thought about throwing things, they threw 150 person barge parties with bringing people from Houston and organized this big event. So I definitely aspired to be like that. So I watched the kind of stuff that they had done and just absorbed that, put my own little spin on it. Did you find that it was easier to find women or men for events? All the guys would come to the event for sure. So, yeah, I think it was definitely harder for women to attend an event, just to have more opportunities. Equally, it's hard to find, you know, quality people that were, you know, socially calibrated on both ends, male and female.
